{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/operacoes-de-um-array-em-javascript/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://devjuniorplus.com.br"}},"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/operacoes-de-um-array-em-javascript/"},"frontmatter":{"description":"Vamos conhecer alguns detalhes importantes que talvez você não saiba.","title":"Operações de um Array em Javascript","date":"30 de agosto de 2020","image":"assets/images/jsmutator.jpg"},"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"computador com codigo aberto em tela\"\n        title=\"computador com codigo aberto em tela\"\n        data-src=\"/static/929c0825dd91df9740d0b81735581403/18e3b/jsmutator.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/929c0825dd91df9740d0b81735581403/46946/jsmutator.jpg 240w,\n/static/929c0825dd91df9740d0b81735581403/55489/jsmutator.jpg 480w,\n/static/929c0825dd91df9740d0b81735581403/18e3b/jsmutator.jpg 960w,\n/static/929c0825dd91df9740d0b81735581403/60e21/jsmutator.jpg 1440w,\n/static/929c0825dd91df9740d0b81735581403/69b48/jsmutator.jpg 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Para facilitar a utilização desse post como pesquisa, dividi em tópicos:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#introducao\">Introdução</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#declarando-um-array-em-js\">Declarando um array em JS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#propriedade-length\">Propriedade length</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#array-mutator-api\">Array Mutator API</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#push\">push</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#pop\">pop</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#unshift\">unshift</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#shift\">shift</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#splice\">splice</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#sort\">sort</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#reverse\">reverse</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fill\">fill</a></li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"introducao\">Introdução</h2>\n<p>Em várias linguagens de programação, temos o tipo de dado <strong>Array</strong>, que nos permitem armazenar vários dados como uma lista. Em Javascript também temos essa estrutura, mas de uma forma um pouco diferente. Os Arrays em JS são na verdade <strong>objetos</strong> que oferecem operações para <strong>acessar</strong> e <strong>manipular</strong> suas propriedades.</p>\n<p>Arrays são similares as <strong>Strings</strong>, sendo que, ambos consistem de uma sequência de elementos que podem ser acessados via índice. Porém, devemos lembrar que <strong><em>Strings são um tipo de dados imutável</em></strong>, o que significa que não podemos alterá-lo. Já os <strong><em>Arrays são mutáveis</em></strong>, o que significa que ao acessar os métodos <strong><em>Array Mutator API</em></strong>, o Array original será alterado.</p>\n<h2 id=\"declarando-um-array-em-js\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">Declarando um array em JS</h2>\n<p>Antes de qualquer coisa, vamos ver as formas de declarar um Array em JS, que basicamente são duas:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Declarar e já atribuir (ou não) seus valores:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Declara um array vazio</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'Maria'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'José'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Joaquim'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Marcos'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> </code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Utilizar a função construtora: </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Array</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Declara utilizando a função construtora</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Array</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Maria'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'José'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Joaquim'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Marcos'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> </code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p><em>A primeira forma a mais usual.</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<h3><strong><em>Nota</em></strong></h3>\n<p>Na segunda forma, temos um detalhe importante que precisa ser mencionado. Veja o exemplo abaixo:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> numeros <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Array</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">9</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">12</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">34</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// => [10, 9, 12, 34]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Isso é o comportamento padrão que esperamos, porém, se passarmos apenas um número para a função construtora, o que acontece é:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> numeros <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Array</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// => Aloca um array com 10 posições vazias</span></code></pre></div>\n</blockquote>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"propriedade-length\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">Propriedade length</h2> \n<p>Podemos descobrir a quantidade de elementos de um Array acessando a propriedade <strong>length</strong>, dessa forma:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> numeros <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">20</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">30</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">40</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">50</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>numeros<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>length<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 5</span></code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<h3><em>Notas</em></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Se no array existir posições vazias, quando acessamos a propriedade <strong>length</strong>, essas posições serão contadas também. Quando o correto seria apenas mostrar a quantidade de elementos válidos dentro do array.</li>\n<li>\n<p>Se inserimos elementos em índices espaçados, o <strong>length</strong> também irá nos retornar um número inesperado. Exemplo:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> numeros <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nnumeros<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nnumeros<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">20</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nnumeros<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">20</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">30</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>numeros<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>length<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Qual o valor será exibido?</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output:</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [10, &lt;9 espaços vazios>, 20, &lt;9 espaços vazios>, 30];</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Resposta = 21 </span></code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</blockquote>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"array-mutator-api\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">Array Mutator API</h2>  \n<blockquote>\n<p>Conjunto de operações que <strong>modificam</strong> o Array original</p>\n</blockquote>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"push\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">push()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>push()</mark> adiciona um novo elemento no <strong>final</strong> do array.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplo:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\npessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">push</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"João\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: [\"Maria\", \"Joaquim\", \"Marcos\", \"João\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<p>O interessante do <mark>push()</mark> é que ele retorna um novo <mark>length()</mark> como resultado.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// length = 3</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">push</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"João\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 4, length agora é 4</span></code></pre></div>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"pop\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">pop()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>pop()</mark> remove um elemento do <strong>final</strong> do array, ou seja, é o inverso do <mark>push()</mark>.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplo:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\npessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">pop</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: Marcos</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<p>Retorna o elemento que foi removido do <strong>final</strong> do array.</p>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"unshift\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">unshift()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>unshift()</mark> adiciona um elemento no <strong>início</strong> do array.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplo:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">unshift</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: 4</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<p>Semelhante ao <mark>push()</mark>, o <mark>unshift()</mark>também retorna o novo <mark>length()</mark>.</p>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"shift\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">shift()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>shift()</mark> remove um elemento do <strong>início</strong> do array, ou seja, o inverso do <mark>unshift()</mark>.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplo:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">shift</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: Marcos</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<p>O <mark>shift()</mark> retorna o elemento que foi removido do <strong>início</strong> do array.</p>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"splice\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">splice()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>splice()</mark> remove, adiciona ou substitui um ou mais elementos em uma determinada posição do array.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Parâmetros:</em></strong> </p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Remove</strong>: (<em>posição<em>do</em>elemento</em>, <em>quantos<em>elementos</em>serão_removidos</em>);</li>\n<li><strong>Adiciona</strong>: (<em>posição<em>do</em>elemento</em>, 0, <em>elemento_1</em>, <em>elemento_2</em>, ..., <em>elemento_n</em>);</li>\n<li><strong>Substitui</strong>: (<em>posição<em>do</em>elemento</em>, <em>quantos<em>elementos</em>serão_substituídos</em>, <em>elemento<em>que</em>será_incluso</em>);</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplos:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Remove</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">splice</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// posição 1, remove 1</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// outuput:</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Joaquim\"]</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// array atual: </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Maria\", \"Marcos\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Adiciona</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">splice</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcia\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Paulo\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// posição 1, remove nenhum, adiciona \"Marcia\" e \"Paulo\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// outuput:</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [] </span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// array atual: </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Maria\", \"Marcia\", \"Paulo\", \"Joaquim\", \"Marcos\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Substitui</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcia\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Paulo\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">splice</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// posição 1, remove 2, adiciona \"Joaquim\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// outuput:</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Marcia\", \"Paulo\"] elementos removidos</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// array atual: </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Maria\", \"Joaquim\", \"Marcos\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Remove</strong>: retorna um array com os elementos removidos;</li>\n<li><strong>Adiciona</strong>: [ ];</li>\n<li><strong>Substitui</strong>: retorna um array com os elementos removidos;</li>\n</ol>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"sort\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">sort()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>sort()</mark> ordena os elementos do array de acordo com a função de ordenação.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplo:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    age<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">30</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    age<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">53</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    age<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">18</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\npessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sort</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">a<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> b</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> a<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>age <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>age<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// ordena de forma crescente</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">//output: </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* [\n**\t{ name: \"Marcos\", age: 18 },\n**  { name: \"Maria\", age: 30 },\n**  { name: \"Joaquim\", age: 53 }\n** ]\n*/</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>(a - b)</strong>: ordena de forma crescente, do menor para o maior;</li>\n<li><strong>(b - a)</strong>: ordena de forma decrescente, do maior para o menor;</li>\n</ol>\n<blockquote>\n<h3><em>Nota</em></h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>return -1 ou 0</strong>: O array fica como está, não altera a ordem;</li>\n<li><strong>return 1</strong>: O array é invertido;</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Para ordenar pelo nome, podemos fazer: </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sort</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">a<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> b</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>a<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;=</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">?</span> <span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Ou</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sort</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">a<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> b</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> a<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">localeCompare</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>b<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Ordena de forma crescente</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><em><mark>localeCompare()</mark> é um método para Strings onde retorna 1 ou -1; utilizado para palavras com acentuação e/ou caracteres específicos de uma região.</em> </p>\n</blockquote>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"reverse\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">reverse()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>reverse()</mark> inverte a ordem dos elementos do array.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplo:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">reverse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: [\"Marcos\", \"Joaquim\", \"Maria\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<p>O array invertido. Para desfazer a inversão, basta realizar outro <mark>reverse()</mark>.</p>\n<br />\n<h2 id=\"fill\" tabindex=\"-1\" style=\"outline: none;\">fill()</h2> \n<p>O método <mark>fill()</mark> preenche os elementos de acordo com a posição de início e fim.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Parâmetros:</em></strong> </p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>1 parâmetro</strong>: (<em>elemento</em>) => Preenche <strong>todo</strong> o array com esse elemento;</li>\n<li><strong>2 parâmetro</strong>: (<em>elemento</em>, <em>posição_inicial</em>) => Preenche da <strong>posição_inicial</strong> até o <strong>final</strong> do array com esse elemento;</li>\n<li><strong>3 parâmetro</strong>: (<em>posição<em>do</em>elemento</em>,  <em>posição_inicial</em>,  <em>posição_final</em>) => Preenche da <strong>posição_inicial</strong> até <strong>posição_final</strong> do array com esse elemento;</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong><em>Exemplo:</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> pessoas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Maria\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Joaquim\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Marcos\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Paulo\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\npessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">fill</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"José\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: [\"José\", \"José\", \"José\", \"José\"]</span>\n\npessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">fill</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"José\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: [\"Maria\", \"José\", \"José\", \"José\"]</span>\n\npessoas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">fill</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"José\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// output: [\"Maria\", \"José\", \"José\", \"Paulo\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong><em>Retorno:</em></strong></p>\n<p>O array preenchido com o elemento passado por parâmetro.</p>","timeToRead":6}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/operacoes-de-um-array-em-javascript/","previousPost":{"fields":{"slug":"/criando-um-todo-list-para-entender-o-react/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Criando um ToDo List para entender o React"}},"nextPost":{"fields":{"slug":"/métodos-de-iteração-de-arrays-em-javascript/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Métodos de iteração de arrays em Javascript"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2037742868","3